goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights were delayed and by how much time on average.

goals.question: What is the average distance of flights?
goals.rationale: This tells us the range of distances covered by flights and the median distance.

goals.question: Which airports have the highest number of flights?
goals.visualization: bar chart of origin and destination
goals.rationale: This tells us which airports are the busiest and have the highest demand for flights.

goals.question: What is the relationship between distance and delay?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of distance and delay
goals.rationale: This tells us if there is any correlation between the distance of the flight and the delay time.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flights over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of date and number of flights
goals.rationale: This tells us if there are any patterns or trends in the number of flights over time.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'].plot(kind='box')
    plt.axhline(y=data['distance'].median(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend(['Median distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].median())])
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['origin'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='blue', alpha=0.5, label='Origin')
    data['destination'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='red', alpha=0.5, label='Destination')
    plt.title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay')
    ax.axhline(y=data['delay'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    flights_per_day = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='flights')
    plt.plot(flights_per_day['date'], flights_per_day['flights'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
